        <item>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:noria.com,2010-06-10:publishing:magazines:rp:35a43cb3-8033-4edd-adea-9cf80104014f</guid>
            <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/motors/~3/hfWGfgJaDZs/stards-associated-with-electric-motor-testing</link>
            <a10:author>
                <a10:name>Noria Corporation</a10:name>
            </a10:author>
            <category>Industry News</category>
            <category>Articles</category>
            <title>Standards associated with electric motor testing</title>
            <description>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;IEEE 519-1992 is the Recommended Practices and Requirements for Harmonic Control in Electric Power Systems. Section 10 - Recommended Practices for Individual Consumers discusses voltage and current distortion limits. These limits are applied to the point of common coupling (PCC), which is the point between the non-linear load and other loads within an industrial plant. For a utility company the PCC is the consumer-utility interface. Maintaining compliance to the harmonic limits at the plant level PCC should ensure that the utility PCC does not exceed the limits specified in Table 10-2-Low-Voltage System Classification and Distortion Limits. The general system limit for Total Harmonic Distortion (THD) is 5 percent and the general system limit for notch depth is 20 percent.&lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;&lt;BR&gt;For more information on how the MCEMAX performs power quality analysis, visit &lt;A href="http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001dGZkoQolA0ZNQT27kNHrb8w9PW9bOmpIU2A_oI8v46GOvbOzOJhDWeOlnv_JoPRt3j3AAcqLR65VKFcRnydV2rs3WVN0xTucxVig5mZULnXzVaG2JGR7FT3gHfP1gD6GJ9Jcz3fFZv_K83Olj7Gpwg==" target=_blank&gt;&lt;U&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;EMAX Fault Zone - Power Quality&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/A&gt;.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;&lt;BR&gt;For more information on the IEEE&amp;nbsp;519&amp;nbsp;standard, go to &lt;A href="http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001dGZkoQolA0aumCyrhcvmGqf3fC-S4Kly4YCapUpTs99IunLFOSwK59CiERLCZYvvjNgKdia1GnSH45qEMJoj6dPbPCSUgbgm_9tHlp6CwHtPvJgHjhA6LihmBeMHzf6iTzLivucpC3lIVxGSRkTBAA==" target=_blank&gt;&lt;U&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;IEEE Standards&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/A&gt;.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/motors/~4/hfWGfgJaDZs" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2008-12-16T00:00:00-06:00</a10:updated>
            <a10:content type="text/html" src="http://reliableplant.com/Read/14922/stards-associated-with-electric-motor-testing" />
        <feedburner:origLink>http://reliableplant.com/Read/14922/stards-associated-with-electric-motor-testing</feedburner:origLink></item>
        <item>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:noria.com,2010-06-10:publishing:magazines:rp:46df6457-65cc-459a-9419-9cf8010334fc</guid>
            <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/motors/~3/E3fGFTGuGr8/stards-associated-with-electric-motor-testing</link>
            <a10:author>
                <a10:name>Noria Corporation</a10:name>
            </a10:author>
            <category>Industry News</category>
            <category>Articles</category>
            <title>Standards associated with electric motor testing</title>
            <description>&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;For the next few weeks we will be reviewing various standards associated with electric motor testing. There are a few very often mentioned standards like the IEEE43 and IEEE95. However, there are other applicable standards worth knowing about where the MCEMAX technology can be utilized to assist in verifying motor acceptability to the standard.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The IEEE 400-2001 is the Guide for Field Testing and Evaluation of the Insulation of Shielded Power Cable Systems. Section 5 - Direct Voltage Testing, discusses low voltage DC testing (LVDC) as tests performed at or below 5000 volts. In this standard the most common LVDC insulation test for shielded power cables is the polarization index test method. The rationale for using DC voltage test equipment is primarily based on the size and power requirements being so excessive for AC voltage test equipment. However, following are abbreviated advantages of performing acceptance and maintenance tests of shielded cables using DC test voltage:&lt;?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoListParagraph style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"&gt;Â·&lt;SPAN style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;Simple, lightweight test equipment compared to AC test equipment&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoListParagraph style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"&gt;Â·&lt;SPAN style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;Readily available power supply for equipment&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoListParagraph style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"&gt;Â·&lt;SPAN style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;Extensive history of successful success on laminated insulation systems&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoListParagraph style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"&gt;Â·&lt;SPAN style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;Very effective at identifying conduction or thermally triggered faults&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoListParagraph style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in; TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="mso-list: Ignore"&gt;Â·&lt;SPAN style="FONT: 7pt 'Times New Roman'"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;Very effective at joint and termination interface problem identification&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"&gt;&lt;SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Arial','sans-serif'; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin"&gt;For more information on the polarization index testing referenced in the IEEE400, visit &lt;A href="http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001AZt84UpAxdvtvaY1VUx-nZsYashnP6sWAHt4GUUKyFkdX2wD6KvAN2J_orOOizItBXUZlMRzLkR5rB51vnoteYD1Jn_A1vm6li4AaBMfaJa4AVEX-WiwhnLTLRfjHTvJVJfDmGxo2pVnW85CQb4xpQmoUfS86OrrfToHt_Eyo7gdHEoaIpUiAHJK5s_jKbP2nhYxYu2gF4-msUcbyHKuow==" target=_blank&gt;&lt;U&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;Identifying Motor Defects Through Fault Zone Analysis&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/A&gt;. For more information on the IEEE 400 article, go to &lt;A href="http://rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001AZt84UpAxdsr2zrobkngor2WmW57uwK_F86U6yUa05XJirFmrA_bE0lAyx2RmOI_xY0rjYZOfidKWFwvihDuRTo1hdxMrXRvRSTSZCt2iPAC9uSARForU9hMZMrWbCYsHvbojEKBDExB8_1-qSclgQ==" target=_blank&gt;&lt;U&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;IEEE Standards&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/A&gt;.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/motors/~4/E3fGFTGuGr8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
